channel.title: Java Installation Error...Urgent
channel.description:
Hey, I recently downloaded Java RE (Runtime Environment) and halfway through the installation my computer shutdown. Now every time i go to re-install it it says it's already installing something and to close this first... but i can't find anywhere that it can be closed... So i tried to uninstall all Java files but the same error message comes up.
Anyone had this problem? If so i need some help :eek:

item.title: Java Installation Error...Urgent
item.dc:creator: @FEARSCAPE FEARSCAPE
item.description:
@FEARSCAPE wrote:

Thats weird…what verison of the JRE is it? I have JRE 5…what do you have?[br][size=1]Posted on: April 08, 2007, 06:08:44 AM[/size][hr]Wait here is the website for JRE 5…
https://sdlc6a.sun.com/ECom/EComActionServlet;jsessionid=B423AD9372CE6050777436F918370BFC.

When you have clicked on the JRE 5 link click ‘Yes’ when the window pops open.
Then click on ‘Accept License Agreement’ at the top. After you have click on it then download the first download on the page. First highlight the box then you should know what do do after that(to download click on ‘Windows Offline Installation, Multi-language’)… If you dont… message me or just post another thing. I hope you can get this download. ;D
